@page "/info/privacy"
<PageTitle>Eldritch Library - Privacy</PageTitle>

<div class="container mt-3">
    <div class="card shadow-sm p-2 p-md-4 mx-auto" style="max-width: 800px;">
        <h3 class="fw-bold mb-1">Privacy Policy for Eldritch Library</h3>
        <p class="text-muted mb-3">Effective Date: Effective Date: Apr 11, 2025</p>

        <hr />

        <h4>1. Introduction</h4>
        <p>
        Welcome to Eldritch Library App Name ("we," "our," or "us"). Your privacy is important to us. 
        This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when 
        you use our Eldritch Library application ("App").
        </p>

        <h4>2. Information We Collect</h4>
        <p>
        When you use our App, we collect and store the following information:
        <ul>
            <li><b>User ID</b>: A unique identifier associated with your account to personalize your 
                experience.</li>
            <li><b>MyCollection Information</b>: Data related to the book collection you track, including
                book ids.</li>
        </ul>
        </p>

        <h4>3. How We Use Your Information</h4>
        <p>
        We use the collected information solely for the following purposes:
        <ul>
            <li>To provide and improve the functionality of the App.</li>
            <li>To personalize your experience and maintain your collection data.</li>
            <li>To ensure the security and integrity of our services.</li>
        </ul>
        </p>

        <h4>4. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h4>
        <p>
        We do <b>not</b> share, sell, rent, or disclose your personal data, including your User ID and collection 
        information, to any external services, third-party companies, or advertisers. All data remains securely
        stored within our database.
        </p>

        <h4>5. Data Storage and Security</h4>
        <p>
        We take industry-standard measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, 
        or destruction, including:
        <ul>
            <li>Secure database storage with access controls.</li>
            <li>Encryption protocols to safeguard sensitive data.</li>
            <li>Regular security assessments and updates.</li>
        </ul>
        </p>

        <h4>6. User Rights and Data Control</h4>
        <p>
        You have the following rights regarding your data:
        <ul>
            <li><b>Access</b>: You can request access to the data stored in your account.</li>
            <li><b>Modification</b>: You can update or modify your book collection data within the App.</li>
            <li><b>Deletion</b>: You can request the deletion of your account and associated data by deleting all 
                of your book collection from our system.</li>
        </ul>
        </p>

        <h4>7. Third-Party Links and Services</h4>
        <p>
        Our App does not integrate with external services or third-party applications that would access your data.
        We use affiliate links on external links to Amazon, EBay, and DriveThruRPG, but no user data is included in 
        those links.
        </p>

        <h4>8. Children's Privacy</h4>
        <p>
        Our App is not intended for individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data 
        from children. If we become aware of such data collection, we will take appropriate steps to delete the 
        information.
        </p>

        <h4>9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h4>
        <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected by the "Effective Date" 
        at the top of this document. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
        </p>

        <h4>10. Contact Us</h4>
        <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us at:
        <ul>
            <li><b>Email</b>:
                <a href="mailto:d20tek.contact@gmail.com?subject=Eldritch%20Library%20Privacy%20Inquiry">
                    d20tek.contact@gmail.com
                </a>
            </li>
        </ul>
        </p>

        <p>
        By using our App, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy.
        </p>
